00:09:58,390 --> 00:09:59,659
You think this is
a joke?

251
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:01,130
You're damn right
this isn't a joke.

252
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,220
I'm being accused of a crime
based on some bullshit email

253
00:10:03,230 --> 00:10:04,529
no one's even seen.

254
00:10:04,530 --> 00:10:06,629
I'd ask if you have that email
on you, Ms. Gibbs,

255
00:10:06,630 --> 00:10:08,929
but I wouldn't want to put you
in the position of lying to me,

256
00:10:08,930 --> 00:10:10,190
so let's have it.

257
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:20,300
<i>♪
♪</i>

258
00:10:20,310 --> 00:10:23,115
This is from a general
Harvard faculty address.

259
00:10:23,116 --> 00:10:26,340
It is. We are working
on tracking down the sender.

260
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:27,719
Well, you'd better
find them,

261
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,789
because without
corroborating testimony,

262
00:10:29,790 --> 00:10:31,989
I'll not only quash
these subpoenas;

263
00:10:31,990 --> 00:10:33,789
I'll toss the entire case.

264
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:38,799
<i>♪
♪</i>

265
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,559
Son of a bitch.
It's Henry Gerard.

266
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,390
Harvey, if Gerard was gonna
say something,

267
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,699
why would he wait
until now?

268
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:46,260
I don't know,
but it's the only goddamn person

269
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:47,469
it could be.

270
00:10:47,470 --> 00:10:48,569
All right, then I'm gonna
go see him.

271
00:10:48,570 --> 00:10:49,800
And do what?

272
00:10:49,810 --> 00:10:51,139
I'm gonna get to him
before Gibbs does,

273
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:52,130
get him to recant.

274
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:53,400
This isn't testimony.

275
00:10:53,410 --> 00:10:55,179
It's a tip to a crime
you actually committed.

276
00:10:55,180 --> 00:10:57,249
I don't care.
We have leverage on Gerard.

277
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,349
Were you in there?

278
00:10:58,350 --> 00:11:00,485
This woman has her sights
on both of us.

279
00:11:00,486 --> 00:11:02,340
You go up to Boston,
she's gonna have people

280
00:11:02,350 --> 00:11:03,780
crawling all over Harvard,

281
00:11:03,790 --> 00:11:05,419
and you're gonna be the one
who led her to Gerard.

282
00:11:05,420 --> 00:11:07,380
I can't just sit here and wait
for the sword to drop.

283
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,489
Wait a second.

284
00:11:08,490 --> 00:11:12,650
You can't go there,
I can't go there,

285
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,060
but I know someone
who can.

286
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,060
Jessica.

287
00:11:20,070 --> 00:11:22,409
I was wondering when you were
gonna show up at my door.

288
00:11:22,410 --> 00:11:23,809
So you've heard
about Mike Ross.

289
00:11:23,810 --> 00:11:26,609
Oh, everybody's heard
about Mike Ross.

290
00:11:26,610 --> 00:11:29,979
Now I finally know what you were
hiding from me the whole time.

291
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:31,609
But what I don't know
is how the hell

292
00:11:31,610 --> 00:11:33,810
you let something like this
happen in the first place.

293
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:35,889
We'll talk about that
in a minute.

294
00:11:35,890 --> 00:11:37,989
But I'm not just here
to apologize

295
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:39,889
for what happened between us.

296
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:42,789
I'm here to ask for your help.

297
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:44,720
You want me to represent
the firm.

298
00:11:44,730 --> 00:11:48,170
If it comes to it,
I want you to represent me.

299
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:52,369
You got a lot of nerve
coming in here to ask me that.

300
00:11:52,370 --> 00:11:53,799
Jeff, please.

301
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,500
I made the mistake
of not trusting you once.

302
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:57,839
I don't want to make
that same mistake again.

303
00:11:57,840 --> 00:12:00,470
Then you're gonna have to tell
me the truth about everything

304
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:03,120
right now, and it's not
gonna be protected

305
00:12:03,121 --> 00:12:05,140
by attorney-client privilege,

306
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:07,790
and you're gonna have to trust
that I'm not gonna turn you in.

307
00:12:07,791 --> 00:12:11,380
I was never worried that
you were gonna turn me in.

308
00:12:11,390 --> 00:12:13,159
I was worried about
putting you in a position

309
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:16,159
where you had to lie.

310
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:19,029
But I was ready to tell you
that night anyway,

311
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:22,100
so I might as well
tell you now.

312
00:12:31,810 --> 00:12:33,250
Rachel,
what's going on?

313
00:12:33,251 --> 00:12:34,600
I just got a call.

314
00:12:34,610 --> 00:12:36,670
They took Donna down to
the U.S. Attorney's office.

315
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:38,120
We have to get down there
right now.

316
00:12:38,121 --> 00:12:40,010
No, we don't.
I'm gonna take care of her.

317
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:41,989
You go ahead and do what
we were gonna do together.

318
00:12:41,990 --> 00:12:43,689
Harvey, Donna getting
taken in changes everything.

319
00:12:43,690 --> 00:12:45,559
It changes nothing,
so stop talking to me

320
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,490
and do what you
have to do.

321
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:58,169
- It was Henry Gerard.
- What?

322
00:12:58,170 --> 00:12:59,739
The person who handed me in
was Henry Gerard.

323
00:12:59,740 --> 00:13:01,139
It was an anonymous email.

324
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:03,309
No way. How would he even know
that you're not a lawyer?

325
00:13:03,310 --> 00:13:05,709
That case we took last year,
he figured it out.

326
00:13:05,710 --> 00:13:07,549
Well, then why would he wait
to turn you in now?

327
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:08,949
I don't know,
but what I do know is,

328
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:10,979
you need to get up there and you
need to get him to take it back.

329
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:12,440
How the hell am I
supposed to do that?

330
00:13:12,450 --> 00:13:13,919
That's what you and I are
gonna figure out right now.

331
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:15,919
Wait a second.
Where's Harvey?

332
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,659
He's got an important
meeting that--

333
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:18,830
What could be
more important than this?

334
00:13:18,820 --> 00:13:19,820
Louis,
it's a personal matter--

335
00:13:19,821 --> 00:13:22,789
Where is he?

336
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:24,390
They brought Donna in
for questioning.

337
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,999
Goddamn it, this is
what I was afraid of.

338
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,229
I'm heading down there
right now.

339
00:13:27,230 --> 00:13:28,720
Louis--Louis,
listen to me.

340
00:13:28,730 --> 00:13:30,229
They're gonna try and put
pressure on Donna

341
00:13:30,230 --> 00:13:31,560
to turn on Harvey,
and the best way

342
00:13:31,570 --> 00:13:34,139
to make that pressure go away
is to make Gerard go away,

343
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:37,239
which can make this whole case
go away.

344
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,770
Give me the goddamn email.

345
00:13:44,180 --> 00:13:45,740
Now, before you go up there,
we're gonna--

346
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:47,249
I'm sorry.
Wait a second.

347
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:49,149
Why would someone who knows
you're guilty

348
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:50,880
call you
a "potential" fraud?

349
00:13:50,890 --> 00:13:52,119
I-I don't know.

350
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,419
He's trying
to cover his ass somehow.

351
00:13:53,420 --> 00:13:56,520
"A potential fraud besmirching
the sacrosanct name

352
00:13:56,530 --> 00:13:58,029
of hallowed
Harvard University"--

353
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:01,100
Louis, we really don't
have time for this. Please.

354
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:04,240
Mike, I know who wrote
this email.

355
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:10,010
It's not Henry Gerard.

356
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,270
Excuse me, miss.

357
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,420
Are you alone, or can
an old man pull up a seat?

358
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:20,040
Hi, Dad.
Oh.

359
00:14:20,990 --> 00:14:24,719
So have you
looked over the deal?

360
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:25,880
I have.

361
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:27,829
And you see the potential
I'm talking about?

362
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:30,200
It's a great project.

363
00:14:30,201 --> 00:14:33,529
But?

364
00:14:33,530 --> 00:14:34,629
I'm not sure
how wise it is

365
00:14:34,630 --> 00:14:37,060
for you to get
back into development.

366
00:14:37,070 --> 00:14:38,539
I understand you would
feel that way

367
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:39,810
after what it did to you,
but--

368
00:14:39,811 --> 00:14:41,700
I feel that way
because of what it did to you.

369
00:14:41,710 --> 00:14:43,009
Donna, I told you.

370
00:14:43,010 --> 00:14:45,779
The banks are crazy for
this kind of thing right now.

371
00:14:45,780 --> 00:14:47,609
All I need is $250,000.

372
00:14:47,610 --> 00:14:49,309
I can get a loan
five times the size.

373
00:14:49,310 --> 00:14:51,110
I don't know; that just
sounds really risky.

374
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,949
Aren't you always telling me
that Harvey says

375
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:55,789
if you want to get ahead,
you need to take risks?

376
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:59,289
That's why
you came to me.

377
00:14:59,290 --> 00:15:01,729
You're not looking for my money;
you're looking for Harvey's.

378
00:15:01,730 --> 00:15:03,489
It would just be
to secure the loan.

379
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:05,090
After the bank gives me
the money, he's free and clear.

380
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,499
Harvey's never gonna
go for that.

381
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,069
I mean, even I know
that's not legal.

382
00:15:08,070 --> 00:15:10,040
Donna, people do
this kind of thing all the time.

383
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:12,060
It's a sleight of hand,
nothing more.

384
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:16,069
Dad, you're doing fine.

385
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:17,970
Do you really need to risk
everything again?

386
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:21,379
Donna, I manage
a real estate office.

387
00:15:21,380 --> 00:15:26,249
Everybody there makes more.
Everybody there is doing better.

388
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:28,449
I used to be better.

389
00:15:28,450 --> 00:15:29,980
I know I can do this.

390
00:15:29,990 --> 00:15:33,059
Please, all you have to do
is ask Harvey.

391
00:15:33,060 --> 00:15:35,090
If he says no,
he says no.

392
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:41,169
Dad, I'm so sorry.

393
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:43,099
Don't worry, sweetie.

394
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:45,239
People have tried to rattle
my cage plenty of times.

395
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:48,309
It's never worked before,
and it's not gonna work now.

396
00:15:48,310 --> 00:15:50,839
That's what I told her.
You're gonna be okay.

397
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:53,270
Donna, can you
give us a minute?

398
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:58,079
Harvey...

399
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,540
Yeah?

400
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:01,089
They're saying
this has to do with that deal

401
00:16:01,090 --> 00:16:02,519
I talked to you about
seven years ago.

402
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:03,619
And?

403
00:16:03,620 --> 00:16:05,559
Is there something
you're not telling me?

404
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:06,989
The only thing
I haven't told you

405
00:16:06,990 --> 00:16:09,120
is that I'm gonna get him
out of this, no matter what.

406
00:16:18,340 --> 00:16:19,705
What the hell did you do?

407
00:16:19,706 --> 00:16:21,130
What are you
talking about?

408
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:22,880
They didn't bring you in here
if you didn't do something

409
00:16:22,870 --> 00:16:24,530
seven years ago, and if
I'm gonna get you out of this,

410
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:25,970
I need to know
what you did.

411
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:28,009
I did what
everybody else did.

412
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:30,370
I inflated my collateral
because you shut me down,

413
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:32,540
so don't come in here telling me
this is my fault.

414
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:34,249
I shut you down
to protect Donna

415
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:36,810
from getting involved
in exactly something like this.

416
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:38,319
This is on you,
not on me.

417
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:41,150
Well, aren't you
high and mighty,

418
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:43,859
coming in here accusing me
of putting my daughter at risk

419
00:16:43,860 --> 00:16:46,190
when the whole reason
she's in the position she's in

420
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:48,669
is because of
something you did?

421
00:16:48,670 --> 00:16:49,899
That's right.

422
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:51,299
They told me this is
because they're trying

423
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:53,460
to get Donna to testify
against you,

424
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,639
and they want me to help them
get her to do it.

425
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:57,239
Then why don't you?

426
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:59,170
Because I know
it would kill her,

427
00:16:59,180 --> 00:17:01,549
and no matter what
you may think,

428
00:17:01,550 --> 00:17:04,050
I would never do anything
to hurt my daughter.

429
00:17:08,120 --> 00:17:09,589
Did you talk to Donna?

430
00:17:09,590 --> 00:17:11,759
I talked to Harvey, and
he said it's gonna be f--

431
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:12,760
I don't care what he says.

432
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:13,760
What are they
coming after her for?

433
00:17:13,761 --> 00:17:14,859
Mike, Harvey asked me
not to--

434
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:16,629
Rachel, what are they
coming after her for?

435
00:17:16,630 --> 00:17:18,299
They're not coming after her
for anything.

436
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:19,670
They're coming
after her father.

437
00:17:19,671 --> 00:17:21,060
What?

438
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:22,569
Turns out he was involved
in some sort of real estate deal

439
00:17:22,570 --> 00:17:23,699
and they're saying it wasn't
on the up-and-up.

440
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:24,769
Goddamn it!

441
00:17:24,770 --> 00:17:27,099
Mike, calm down.
It's nothing.

442
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:28,630
Harvey's gonna get them
out of it.

443
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:31,079
Look, it's really
just a minor violation,

444
00:17:31,080 --> 00:17:33,510
and no one would even care
if it weren't for--

445
00:17:34,850 --> 00:17:37,020
Me. You were just about to say
if it weren't for me.

446
00:17:37,021 --> 00:17:38,021
- Mike, I--
- That's it.

447
00:17:38,022 --> 00:17:39,149
I'm pleading guilty.

448
00:17:39,150 --> 00:17:40,319
I'm gonna take
the reduced sentence,

449
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:41,320
I'm gonna do the time,
and all of this

450
00:17:41,321 --> 00:17:42,619
is gonna go away
once and for all.

451
00:17:42,620 --> 00:17:44,489
That's not an option,
and you know it.

452
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:46,459
The only reason
they went after Donna's dad

453
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:47,989
is to get to Harvey
and Jessica.

454
00:17:47,990 --> 00:17:50,550
If you plead guilty, all you're
gonna do is help them do that,

455
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,620
so you're either gonna
turn on the two of them

456
00:17:52,630 --> 00:17:55,599
or you're gonna fight this thing
out till the end.

457
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,069
We need to talk.

458
00:17:57,070 --> 00:17:58,099
About what?

459
00:17:58,100 --> 00:17:59,299
About what we're
going to do

460
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:01,460
if that prosecutor
gets ahold of those subpoenas.

461
00:18:01,470 --> 00:18:03,869
You mean what we're gonna do
about the letter that Mike has

462
00:18:03,870 --> 00:18:05,470
that proves you knew
he was a fraud.

463
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:08,009
Yes, that's what I mean.

464
00:18:08,010 --> 00:18:09,440
I'm assuming you were
smart enough

465
00:18:09,450 --> 00:18:11,249
to destroy that thing
the second they let you out.

466
00:18:11,250 --> 00:18:12,890
And I'm assuming you
destroyed the affidavit

467
00:18:12,891 --> 00:18:15,880
that you had Rachel sign saying
she knew the truth about me.

468
00:18:15,890 --> 00:18:17,689
I didn't,

469
00:18:17,690 --> 00:18:20,059
but I had the same conversation
with Louis, we worked it out,

470
00:18:20,060 --> 00:18:21,159
and I'm here to tell you

471
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:23,330
I will get rid of mine
if you get rid of yours.

472
00:18:24,830 --> 00:18:26,799
I knew it;
you're actually considering

473
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,499
turning your back
on me and Harvey.

474
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,969
I'm not turning my back
on anyone,

475
00:18:29,970 --> 00:18:31,539
but we both know
you've done some things

476
00:18:31,540 --> 00:18:34,069
that make me question
whether or not I can trust you.

477
00:18:34,070 --> 00:18:36,600
Well, then,
the least you can do

478
00:18:36,610 --> 00:18:39,079
is find the time to speak
with my attorney

479
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,750
before that ruling
comes down.

480
00:18:40,751 --> 00:18:41,840
Your attorney?

481
00:18:41,850 --> 00:18:43,849
I'm sure
you've heard of him.

482
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:46,750
His name's Jeff Malone.

483
00:18:49,550 --> 00:18:51,550
You're even lower
than I thought you were,

484
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,259
and I didn't even think
that was possible.

485
00:18:53,260 --> 00:18:54,729
Coming from someone
with your moral compass,

486
00:18:54,730 --> 00:18:55,959
I take that
as a compliment.

487
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:56,995
What gives you the right

488
00:18:56,996 --> 00:18:58,590
to come after
my secretary's father?

489
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,729
I'm not the one
prosecuting him.

490
00:18:59,730 --> 00:19:01,269
It just so happens that
one of my colleagues

491
00:19:01,270 --> 00:19:03,769
is going after him on
a completely unrelated matter.

492
00:19:03,770 --> 00:19:05,569
Bullshit, the only reason
you're doing this

493
00:19:05,570 --> 00:19:07,909
is to put pressure on Donna
to come after me.

494
00:19:07,910 --> 00:19:10,239
Well, now that you mention it,
the judge did say

495
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:12,745
I needed something tying you
to Mike Ross's fraud

496
00:19:12,746 --> 00:19:14,139
in order to get
those subpoenas,

497
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:16,070
and maybe that something
is Donna Paulsen.

498
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,080
I should ask her.

499
00:19:17,081 --> 00:19:18,219
You already did ask her,

500
00:19:18,220 --> 00:19:19,449
and now you're
manufacturing

501
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:21,549
a bullshit case
against an innocent man,

502
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:23,449
and I'm gonna make sure
you pay for it.

503
00:19:23,450 --> 00:19:25,310
He's not in here
because of what I did.

504
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:27,219
He's in here
because of what you did.

505
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:29,750
So instead of blaming me,
take a look in the mirror,

506
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:32,699
'cause all you have to do
is admit what you did,

507
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,470
and all of this
goes away.

508
00:19:37,470 --> 00:19:39,000
<i>♪
♪</i>

509
00:19:51,580 --> 00:19:54,279
Louis.

510
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:56,710
What are you doing here?

511
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,919
You know why I'm here.

512
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:01,320
I'm here because of this.

513
00:20:01,330 --> 00:20:02,459
I don't know
what that is.

514
00:20:02,460 --> 00:20:04,395
Please, your language
is all over it.

515
00:20:04,396 --> 00:20:07,090
You might as well have
signed your name.

516
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:09,129
What I want to know is why.

517
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,530
I got a call
about an article

518
00:20:14,540 --> 00:20:17,675
on Mike Ross's meteoric rise
to junior partner.

519
00:20:17,676 --> 00:20:18,900
Problem is, I remember

520
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:21,050
every student
that's ever gone here,

521
00:20:21,051 --> 00:20:23,509
and there is no Mike Ross,

522
00:20:23,510 --> 00:20:26,879
so I double-checked
my file room,

523
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:28,140
and then I sent this.

524
00:20:28,150 --> 00:20:30,210
Sheila, you are
messing with my firm.

525
00:20:30,220 --> 00:20:31,959
Why didn't you
come to me first?

526
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:33,689
Because it didn't occur to me
that I had to.

527
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:36,529
That is bullshit!

528
00:20:36,530 --> 00:20:38,329
You reported it
anonymously

529
00:20:38,330 --> 00:20:39,599
because you didn't want
to look bad.

530
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,170
You didn't trust me
to keep you out of it.

531
00:20:41,171 --> 00:20:42,729
No, I reported it
anonymously

532
00:20:42,730 --> 00:20:45,560
because I was ashamed that
it happened on my watch,

533
00:20:45,570 --> 00:20:48,169
but I'm not gonna stand by
while somebody besmirches

534
00:20:48,170 --> 00:20:50,169
the good name
of Harvard University.

535
00:20:50,170 --> 00:20:52,400
You have no proof that
Mike Ross besmirched anything.

536
00:20:52,410 --> 00:20:54,279
Why are you
defending this lowlife?

537
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:55,579
Because if you'd
come to me first,

538
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:58,179
I could have stopped
this whole thing from happening.

539
00:20:58,180 --> 00:21:00,240
Oh, my God.

540
00:21:02,290 --> 00:21:05,719
You knew.

541
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:08,620
Sheila, please, you don't
know him like I know him.

542
00:21:08,630 --> 00:21:12,399
What exactly are you
doing here, Louis?

543
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:14,470
I want you to retract
that email.

544
00:21:14,471 --> 00:21:18,190
Tell 'em that you made
a mistake; you found the file.

545
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,799
I can't do that.

546
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:22,230
Sheila, please.

547
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:26,079
When we broke up,
I forced myself to accept it,

548
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:29,479
because ultimately I knew
we wanted different things,

549
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:33,519
but it killed me, because I also
knew that we were soul mates.

550
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:38,359
But the fact that you're
asking me to do this...

551
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:41,430
We are not soul mates.

552
00:21:45,430 --> 00:21:47,299
I'm begging you.

553
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:48,869
At least don't
come forward.

554
00:21:48,870 --> 00:21:51,940
I never was gonna
come forward, Louis.

555
00:21:53,940 --> 00:21:56,140
Now leave me alone.

556
00:22:01,110 --> 00:22:08,080
<i>♪
♪</i>

557
00:22:08,090 --> 00:22:10,619
I thought I'd find you here.

558
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:12,089
How are you doing?

559
00:22:12,090 --> 00:22:13,530
Well, they're coming
after my father

560
00:22:13,531 --> 00:22:14,720
for something he didn't do.

561
00:22:14,730 --> 00:22:15,829
How do you think I'm doing?

562
00:22:15,830 --> 00:22:17,859
I'm sorry.
Do you want to be alone?

563
00:22:17,860 --> 00:22:19,590
No. I'm sorry. It's just--

564
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:21,569
Donna, please,
you're worried sick

565
00:22:21,570 --> 00:22:22,669
for someone you love.

566
00:22:22,670 --> 00:22:24,199
I get it.

567
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:26,499
It's just, last year
my life was in Harvey's hands,

568
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,900
and he told me that my worrying
about what would happen

569
00:22:28,910 --> 00:22:31,080
if he lost would only make it
more likely for him to lose.

570
00:22:31,070 --> 00:22:32,939
I know, and you can't help
but worry about it,

571
00:22:32,940 --> 00:22:34,000
because it's your father.

572
00:22:34,010 --> 00:22:35,010
No, I can't.

573
00:22:35,011 --> 00:22:36,240
And you can't help
wondering,

574
00:22:36,250 --> 00:22:38,679
if it comes down to it,
what will you do?

575
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:40,240
What?

576
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:43,149
No, Rachel, how can you
even ask me that?

577
00:22:43,150 --> 00:22:45,580
I get it.

578
00:22:45,590 --> 00:22:46,830
Because if it
comes down to it,

579
00:22:46,831 --> 00:22:48,720
you want Mike to consider
turning on Harvey.

580
00:22:48,730 --> 00:22:50,029
That's not what I said.

581
00:22:50,030 --> 00:22:51,699
You know, if you're
just here to get me

582
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:53,529
to think about doing that,
I don't need that right now.

583
00:22:53,530 --> 00:22:54,869
No, no, no, Donna,
I came in here

584
00:22:54,870 --> 00:22:57,429
because I care about you
and I am--

585
00:22:58,570 --> 00:23:00,210
I'm sorry that
I even brought it up.

586
00:23:00,211 --> 00:23:01,360
Are you sorry?

587
00:23:01,370 --> 00:23:02,360
Excuse me?

588
00:23:02,370 --> 00:23:03,569
Do you think
that I don't know

589
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:04,970
that all your problems
are solved

590
00:23:04,980 --> 00:23:06,479
if I tell them
that Harvey did this?

591
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:09,415
No, Donna, all of my problems
are solved if Mike tells them.

592
00:23:09,416 --> 00:23:11,970
But, yes, my life gets
a whole lot better

593
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:13,910
if Harvey takes responsibility
for what he did.

594
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:15,089
What he did was
give Mike a chance

595
00:23:15,090 --> 00:23:16,389
to make something
of himself.

596
00:23:16,390 --> 00:23:19,689
Which is why Mike's never
gonna turn on him.

597
00:23:19,690 --> 00:23:21,059
But you know what?

598
00:23:21,060 --> 00:23:23,595
I would be lying if I said
it didn't cross my mind

599
00:23:23,596 --> 00:23:25,720
that maybe Mike should think
about making a deal.

600
00:23:25,730 --> 00:23:27,999
And you can't tell me that
since they picked up your father

601
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,799
that the thought hasn't
crossed yours too.

602
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,799
Well, thinking about it
and talking about it

603
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,430
aren't the same thing,

604
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:38,510
and right now, I'm focusing
on having faith in Harvey.

605
00:23:42,780 --> 00:23:43,879
Louis, what the hell?

606
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,019
I've been looking for you
all morning.

607
00:23:45,020 --> 00:23:47,279
What happened?
It was her.

608
00:23:48,690 --> 00:23:49,690
And?

609
00:23:49,691 --> 00:23:51,160
She's not gonna
retract the email.

610
00:23:51,161 --> 00:23:53,150
Shit.
What did she say?

611
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:55,289
Oh, what the hell
do you think she said?

612
00:23:55,290 --> 00:23:59,150
Said she knows you're a fraud,
she's not gonna take it back,

613
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:01,020
and now that she's figured out
that I've been a part of it,

614
00:24:01,030 --> 00:24:02,460
she can't stand
the sight of me.

615
00:24:02,470 --> 00:24:03,940
All right, then we need
to think of something else--

616
00:24:03,941 --> 00:24:05,790
Oh, did you just hear
what I just said?

617
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:09,260
She can't stand
the sight of me.

618
00:24:09,270 --> 00:24:11,200
Louis, I know
you're feeling bad,

619
00:24:11,210 --> 00:24:13,009
but right now,
Donna is under the gun.

620
00:24:13,010 --> 00:24:14,479
What do you want me
to do about that?

621
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:15,879
I don't know, but if she
doesn't retract that email

622
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,880
and they find her--

623
00:24:16,881 --> 00:24:18,219
No, they're not gonna
find her,

624
00:24:18,220 --> 00:24:20,549
because she sent it
from a general faculty email

625
00:24:20,550 --> 00:24:23,489
because she's ashamed of herself
like she's ashamed of me.

626
00:24:23,490 --> 00:24:26,259
And this is all your fault,
so get the hell out of my office

627
00:24:26,260 --> 00:24:29,230
instead of trying to figure out
a way to cover your goddamn ass!

628
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:35,199
You can believe this or not,
Louis, but right this second,

629
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:38,029
I'm actually looking out
for Donna.

630
00:24:38,030 --> 00:24:40,299
I'm sorry, Mike.

631
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:42,900
Right this second,
I cannot help you.

632
00:24:52,650 --> 00:24:53,650
Good, you're here.

633
00:24:53,651 --> 00:24:55,049
Listen, I need you
to take care of--

634
00:24:55,050 --> 00:24:56,449
Before we get
to the game plan,

635
00:24:56,450 --> 00:24:57,780
I need to know what's going on
with Donna's father.

636
00:24:57,790 --> 00:24:58,790
I'm taking care of it.

637
00:24:58,791 --> 00:25:00,959
Did you get Louis
to go see Gerard?

638
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:03,059
It wasn't Gerard.
It was Sheila Sazs.

639
00:25:03,060 --> 00:25:04,689
You gotta be kidding me.

640
00:25:04,690 --> 00:25:06,150
Louis told his girlfriend
about you?

641
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:08,790
No, Harvey, you told
your girlfriend about me.

642
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,469
Louis risked his neck
to get Sheila

643
00:25:10,470 --> 00:25:12,569
to take that email back
to save our asses.

644
00:25:12,570 --> 00:25:14,039
What are you
so bent out of shape for?

645
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:15,939
I'm bent out of shape
because he couldn't do it,

646
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:17,880
and on top of that, Donna's dad
is only in this mess

647
00:25:17,881 --> 00:25:20,300
because of what we did,
and you won't let me help.

648
00:25:20,310 --> 00:25:21,979
That's right, Mike;
I won't let you help,

649
00:25:21,980 --> 00:25:23,249
because you're
under investigation

650
00:25:23,250 --> 00:25:24,549
for being a fraud.

651
00:25:24,550 --> 00:25:25,949
You're under investigation
too, and if we're

652
00:25:25,950 --> 00:25:27,749
supposed to act like there's
nothing to be ashamed of,

653
00:25:27,750 --> 00:25:29,810
then let's act like there's
nothing to be ashamed of.

654
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:31,519
Okay, that's all
well and good, Mike,

655
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:34,150
but I'm the one representing
Donna's father, not you,

656
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:36,429
which means I'm the only one
with a credible reason

657
00:25:36,430 --> 00:25:38,000
to pay a visit to the banker
that gave him

658
00:25:37,990 --> 00:25:39,250
that shitty loan
in the first place.

659
00:25:39,260 --> 00:25:40,920
Harvey,
this is killing me!

660
00:25:43,930 --> 00:25:44,930
<i>♪
♪</i>

661
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:47,369
I have to do something.

662
00:25:47,370 --> 00:25:49,269
Right now,
the best thing you can do

663
00:25:49,270 --> 00:25:50,630
is think about what
we're gonna do

664
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,779
if they put it together
about Louis's girlfriend,

665
00:25:52,780 --> 00:25:57,079
because if they find her,
we're in deep shit.

666
00:25:57,080 --> 00:26:01,850
<i>♪
♪</i>

667
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:15,440
<i>♪
♪</i>

668
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:26,639
How did you find me here?

669
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:27,870
I remember
every game you have

670
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:29,315
from our work
on your case.

671
00:26:29,316 --> 00:26:30,970
And I knew I had to find you
at a place

672
00:26:30,980 --> 00:26:33,140
where we couldn't be bothered
by anyone from Harvard.

673
00:26:33,150 --> 00:26:35,589
Because everyone from Harvard
now knows you didn't go there.

674
00:26:35,590 --> 00:26:37,060
Which is why I need
someone from Harvard

675
00:26:37,061 --> 00:26:38,250
to tell them
that I did.

676
00:26:38,260 --> 00:26:39,489
Are you crazy?

677
00:26:39,490 --> 00:26:40,789
No, I'm smart.

678
00:26:40,790 --> 00:26:42,350
All they have is
an anonymous tip

679
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:43,759
and no corroborating
evidence.

680
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:46,320
You sign this affidavit saying
that I was in your class,

681
00:26:46,330 --> 00:26:47,729
their whole case
gets dismissed.

682
00:26:47,730 --> 00:26:48,760
And what if it doesn't?

683
00:26:48,770 --> 00:26:50,269
Then I go to trial.

684
00:26:50,270 --> 00:26:51,439
This is reasonable doubt.

685
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,210
I get acquitted,
they can never try me again.

686
00:26:53,211 --> 00:26:55,830
Or it's not reasonable doubt,
you don't get acquitted,

687
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:57,239
and I go to jail
for perjury.

688
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:59,039
I remember when you were
willing to commit perjury

689
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:01,340
and we didn't just stop you;
we saved your ass.

690
00:27:01,350 --> 00:27:04,179
I don't care. I'm not
risking everything for you.

691
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:06,679
This isn't just for me,
all right?

692
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:09,780
They are coming after everyone
that I care about.

693
00:27:09,790 --> 00:27:12,019
I feel for you, Mike,

694
00:27:12,020 --> 00:27:14,050
which is why I never turned
you in in the first place,

695
00:27:14,060 --> 00:27:16,729
but I can't do
what you're asking.

696
00:27:16,730 --> 00:27:18,299
And what if I
anonymously told Harvard

697
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:22,199
that you took a bribe
from a student for a grade?

698
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:24,239
You willing to bet everything
that I won't do that?

699
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:26,199
You do what you have to do,

700
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,760
but I'm not putting
my life in jeopardy

701
00:27:27,770 --> 00:27:29,600
by signing
that goddamn thing.

702
00:27:31,510 --> 00:27:34,479
Wait a minute,
wait, wait.

703
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:36,020
What if I had a way
that you could help me

704
00:27:36,021 --> 00:27:37,470
without having to
perjure yourself?

705
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,440
And how exactly
would I do that?

706
00:27:39,450 --> 00:27:40,919
It's right
in your wheelhouse.

707
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,460
We're playing poker too.

708
00:27:42,461 --> 00:27:45,050
I just--

709
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:47,090
I just need you
to help me bluff.

710
00:27:49,660 --> 00:27:52,999
Harvey, I need to ask you
to do something.

711
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,729
Of course, Donna.
I'd do anything for you.

712
00:27:54,730 --> 00:27:57,590
Well, it isn't for me.
It's for my father.

713
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:59,760
He wanted to know
if you would consider

714
00:27:59,770 --> 00:28:03,269
investing
in his real estate project.

715
00:28:03,270 --> 00:28:04,430
I'm sorry.
I can't do that.

716
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:05,970
You just said that you would
do anything for me.

717
00:28:05,980 --> 00:28:09,849
I meant I'd consider anything,
and I just did.

718
00:28:09,850 --> 00:28:11,379
You haven't even
looked at it.

719
00:28:11,380 --> 00:28:13,610
I don't need to.

720
00:28:13,620 --> 00:28:15,755
You're family to me,
he's family to you,

721
00:28:15,756 --> 00:28:17,980
and you don't invest money
with family.

722
00:28:17,990 --> 00:28:19,059
That's not what you said

723
00:28:19,060 --> 00:28:20,389
when Marcus needed money
for his restaurant.

724
00:28:20,390 --> 00:28:22,050
- That's different.
- Why?

725
00:28:22,060 --> 00:28:24,300
Because Marcus actually knew
what the hell he was doing.

726
00:28:26,430 --> 00:28:27,629
You know what, Harvey?

727
00:28:27,630 --> 00:28:29,229
If you don't want to invest,
don't invest,

728
00:28:29,230 --> 00:28:30,730
but I don't need
a lecture from you

729
00:28:30,740 --> 00:28:33,710
on what a bad businessman
my father is.

730
00:28:34,970 --> 00:28:36,069
Yes, you do.

731
00:28:36,070 --> 00:28:37,130
Oh, really?
Why's that?

732
00:28:37,140 --> 00:28:38,570
Because if I know you,

733
00:28:38,580 --> 00:28:40,809
you're thinking of giving him
access to your 401.

734
00:28:40,810 --> 00:28:42,140
So? What if I am?

735
00:28:42,150 --> 00:28:44,919
Donna, this man lost
your family's money once.

736
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,549
You're gonna give him
the chance to do it again?

737
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:48,819
Harvey,
this man is my father,

738
00:28:48,820 --> 00:28:50,859
and he has been there for me
my whole life.

739
00:28:50,860 --> 00:28:53,059
And I know what happened
between you and your mother,

740
00:28:53,060 --> 00:28:54,989
but don't you judge him
for what she did.

741
00:28:54,990 --> 00:28:57,450
How dare you? This has
nothing to do with that.

742
00:28:57,460 --> 00:28:59,220
You have a blind spot
when it comes to him.

743
00:28:59,230 --> 00:29:00,429
I'm trying to protect you.

744
00:29:00,430 --> 00:29:03,460
Well, you're not.
You're being an asshole.

