Well, now you do.

991
00:38:32,070 --> 00:38:35,169
So you'll destroy that
if I give you mine?

992
00:38:35,170 --> 00:38:38,600
I'm an attorney.
I can't destroy evidence.

993
00:38:38,610 --> 00:38:42,680
But you?
You can do whatever you want.

994
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:46,140
You trust me to do that?

995
00:38:47,250 --> 00:38:50,010
No, Mike.

996
00:38:50,020 --> 00:38:51,920
Jessica does.

997
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:08,669
Louis, I need you
to sit down.

998
00:39:08,670 --> 00:39:10,230
What is it?
What happened?

999
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,839
Is your father okay?
I'll go down there right now.

1000
00:39:11,840 --> 00:39:13,270
He's fine.
Harvey took care of it.

1001
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:14,849
Oh, well, then I don't need
to sit down.

1002
00:39:14,850 --> 00:39:18,119
'Cause whatever it is,
if you're okay, I'll be okay.

1003
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:20,219
Sheila came forward.

1004
00:39:20,220 --> 00:39:22,089
What?

1005
00:39:22,090 --> 00:39:25,160
She admitted she was
the one to write the email.

1006
00:39:27,230 --> 00:39:28,529
That's not possible.

1007
00:39:28,530 --> 00:39:29,900
She promised me
she wouldn't do that.

1008
00:39:29,901 --> 00:39:32,420
I'm sorry, Louis,
but she did.

1009
00:39:37,670 --> 00:39:39,499
I need to be alone.

1010
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:41,300
Louis, I don't think
this is the time for you to--

1011
00:39:41,310 --> 00:39:43,110
I said get out.

1012
00:39:53,650 --> 00:39:54,640
He did it?

1013
00:39:54,650 --> 00:39:55,710
He did.

1014
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:57,259
What did you say to him?

1015
00:39:57,260 --> 00:39:59,919
I told him
how much it cost you,

1016
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:01,720
and then I did
what we talked about.

1017
00:40:01,730 --> 00:40:03,999
Well, it's a good thing
you did,

1018
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:06,000
because those subpoenas
just came down.

1019
00:40:11,470 --> 00:40:12,839
Jessica, I don't know
that I've ever been

1020
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:15,809
much of a spiritual person,

1021
00:40:15,810 --> 00:40:17,839
but I would be lying
if I didn't admit

1022
00:40:17,840 --> 00:40:20,900
that sometimes I think
God has a plan.

1023
00:40:20,910 --> 00:40:22,309
What are you saying?

1024
00:40:22,310 --> 00:40:24,270
I'm saying that maybe
he's trying to show you

1025
00:40:24,280 --> 00:40:29,680
that there's more to life
than Pearson Specter Litt.

1026
00:40:29,690 --> 00:40:31,459
I'm not gonna be
your attorney on this one.

1027
00:40:31,460 --> 00:40:34,359
I think you can find
someone better.

1028
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:35,989
No.

1029
00:40:35,990 --> 00:40:38,390
I trust you,
and there's no way

1030
00:40:38,400 --> 00:40:40,729
I find someone
that I trust more.

1031
00:40:40,730 --> 00:40:44,060
Then find me when
this is all over,

1032
00:40:44,070 --> 00:40:47,310
and we'll see if we can put
that trust to better use.

1033
00:40:52,140 --> 00:40:54,600
Gretchen, whatever it is,
it can wait till tomorrow.

1034
00:40:54,610 --> 00:40:56,940
This can't wait.

1035
00:40:56,950 --> 00:41:00,519
I want to apologize to you.

1036
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,119
For what?

1037
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:05,519
When Jack Soloff nominated
Mike Ross for partner,

1038
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:07,620
I know it hurt Harvey
a little,

1039
00:41:07,630 --> 00:41:10,559
because he wanted to be
the one to do it,

1040
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:14,590
so I called the "ABA Journal"
to write an article about Mike.

1041
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:17,340
I wanted to surprise Harvey
with it.

1042
00:41:20,040 --> 00:41:24,740
You're saying the article
that tipped Sheila off was you?

1043
00:41:25,940 --> 00:41:28,470
Yes.

1044
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:30,279
Why are you
telling me this?

1045
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:34,310
Because I'm sorry.

1046
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:37,089
And if anyone ever asks,
I'll deny ever saying this,

1047
00:41:37,090 --> 00:41:40,760
but...I know
you all knew.

1048
00:41:43,190 --> 00:41:44,920
And I'm with you.

1049
00:41:49,570 --> 00:41:51,640
Hey.
Hey.

1050
00:41:54,510 --> 00:41:55,909
What's the matter?

1051
00:41:55,910 --> 00:41:59,209
I know I said I don't want you
to keep things from me,

1052
00:41:59,210 --> 00:42:00,679
but I don't want to keep things
from you either.

1053
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:02,149
What are you
keeping from me?

1054
00:42:02,150 --> 00:42:04,819
It's actually
good and bad news.

1055
00:42:04,820 --> 00:42:07,190
We had a chance to get this
whole case thrown out today,

1056
00:42:07,191 --> 00:42:11,010
and it didn't work,
but we did get Donna off,

1057
00:42:11,020 --> 00:42:14,350
and for the first time,
I actually started to believe

1058
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:16,629
we can get out of this thing.

1059
00:42:16,630 --> 00:42:19,029
And why were you afraid
to admit that to me?

1060
00:42:19,030 --> 00:42:23,029
Because I didn't want to
get your hopes up.

1061
00:42:23,030 --> 00:42:25,230
And I didn't really
believe it before.

1062
00:42:30,140 --> 00:42:31,170
Yeah, what's up?

1063
00:42:31,180 --> 00:42:32,909
Sheila Sazs came forward,

1064
00:42:32,910 --> 00:42:34,349
which means they're gonna
try and pit us all

1065
00:42:34,350 --> 00:42:37,420
against each other
even more.

